.Im MicroEmacs variable|buffer|indent
.so me.tni
.TH $indent-width 5
.XI $indent-width - "Global indentation width in characters"
.XI $buffer-indent-width - "Buffer indentation width in characters"
.SH NAME
.na
.Me "|$indent-width"
$indent-width \- Global indentation width in characters
.Me "|$buffer-indent-width"
$buffer-indent-width \- Buffer indentation width in characters
.Me $a
.ad
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fB$indent-width\fR
.br
\fB$buffer-indent-width\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B $indent-width
defines the default  indentation width assumed by the editor, this defines the
number of characters the 
.Ht indent 2 
command  should  use for  indenting  text.  Once the value is set then all new
buffers that are subsequently created assume an indent value of 
.BR $indent-width .
The default value when omitted is 4 characters.
.PP
.B $buffer-indent-width
specifies the indent to use in a buffer, the value of 
.B $indent-width
is used as a default when the buffer is created. Modification of the 
.B $buffer-indent-width
value  causes  the  buffer  indentation  width to be  modified.  The  value is
typically set by the  \fBfhook-xxx\fR  macro when  initializing a buffer using
the 
.Hl "Language Templates" languageTemplates 2 .
.SH NOTES
.B $buffer-indent-width
and 
.B $indent-width
were introduced into \*(mS in November 2004.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.na
.Ht indent 2 .
.br
.Hl "Language Templates" languageTemplates 2 .
.ad
.FH
